<subSubSection id="F2661E3A13665DE5AD82ED2662EE6A3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0898DDB2B46ACDECFE1DE708225045C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D9C533C4AD35F01666928178135E724" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
For detailed morphology see 
<bibRefCitation id="2CE1683BDD2DD3E41EEE9CB020594059" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1347 - 1415" refId="B6" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Loebl, I, 1997. Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Journal of Natural History 31: 1347 - 1415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" title="Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" volume="31" year="1997">
Cuccodoro and 
<normalizedToken id="2188441C901BA710B11F4C17B375AD88" originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
. Combined length of head, pronotum, and elytra 1.6-1.9 mm; maximal pronotal width = 0.9-1.1 mm. Body and appendages (Figs 
<figureCitation id="0FE709102FD7A7A72D391480D35E35A2" captionStart="Figures 7–9" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 7 - 9. Megarthrus hemipterus (Illiger): habitus, male: dorsal 7 ventral 8 and lateral 9 views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures7-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578545" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">7-9</figureCitation>
) rust brown; head markedly darker with frons slightly paler than vertex. Anterior frontal margin slightly carinate, evenly convex in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<caption id="1030CCAB668680F0A0B30E2BC244552F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures7-9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578545" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figures 7–9" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="7B254FBE13206239DD546AE9B74389F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="7DF2B421BCCF6C29A55B3B8A9FEAA5B4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Figures 7-9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1BF47937C20A054799A6E1B62D0DBA02" baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1794" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus hemipterus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis id="FDF43057ACAB2E85327413EE90359E80" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Illiger): habitus, male: dorsal 
<emphasis id="1706457035C7593DD384AB08EBC35E58" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">7</emphasis>
ventral 
<emphasis id="095378EC81692F67737BDCE556083632" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">8</emphasis>
and lateral 
<emphasis id="87FCCB5C6F9D076F8CBB4F5299D7DC39" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">9</emphasis>
views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8A72ACF5ECFA339AC1C9892C5156453B" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="4A7233C791C44BE273DF008ACFFB9179" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="7966AE889918F1EEE25F6A489B6695F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Protibia fairly straight and slightly enlarged toward apex, evenly, with adventral side markedly depressed transversely at middle. Mesotrochanter with about a dozen of peg-like setae arranged in two rows. Mesofemur slightly arcuate and slightly swollen. Mesotibia subangulate, bearing peg-like setae arranged in one row. Metatrochanter and metafemur slightly swollen; posterior margin of metatrochanter evenly arcuate; inner margin of metafemur slightly concave in ventral view, forming sharp ridge on entire length. Metatibia swollen, at middle forming conspicuous tooth-like process projecting above flattened apical portion of metatibia; metatibial peg-like setae arranged in 1-2 rows on apical third, the latter group of 15-20, discontinuously with more than 12 peg-like setae arranged in two rows on distal side of tooth-like process; proximal side of tooth-like process broad and flat, bearing 4-10 scattered peg-like setae. Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation id="20AD473CC8B37D8B76BEBD91F690136C" captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1089FB4D47D021AD5ACDB09A94F3C3A7" captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">15</figureCitation>
) with ventral wall not narrowed at base and gradually narrowed to mucronate apex in ventral view, with ventral fairly straight to apex in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7A887EFE3FA358191832117CFA7F551" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="BBA52AE88AE09024ECA7F00D42A4A570" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B0E7411AD08250FB63FF56178C97E53C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Female</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Gonocoxal plate with lateral portions of dorsobasal margin straight to middle portion forming small blunt process slightly projecting anterad. Dorsal part of genitalia with arcuate sclerite wider at middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DEB7DD65313C01C284E29A3D0803E1EC" captionStart="Figures 10–18" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 10 - 18. Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer (10, 13, 16) M. flavolimbatus Cameron (11, 14, 17) M. hemipterus (Illiger) (12, 15, 18) male: aedeagus in ventral (10 - 12) and lateral (13 - 15) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (16 - 18) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="2361557555CCD529F8118DB353FBF009" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures10-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578546" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figures 10–18" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="12796BB75F93BAD0EB5562EAB89913B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="EE12657F1397C158410E97E64165FAFA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Figures 10-18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5055B74AEBA3FDD680882E9926DBDB21" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus dentipes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentipes">
<emphasis id="3DF95B7EE878CD2F8C88272CA7DA3A13" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus dentipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bernhauer (
<emphasis id="A7C647D2D6D66060917AD4A7F40F9598" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">10, 13, 16</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="A1CF56A2705D55D9B91B161771343AB0" genus="M." lsidName="M. flavolimbatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="flavolimbatus">
<emphasis id="1E9197443832C295E8F9ACC698E5241B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. flavolimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cameron (
<emphasis id="A1A447D0C45230B48695D8E084CAA364" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">11, 14, 17</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="11518D731CF6284F675A3610CF4C3E65" genus="M." lsidName="M. hemipterus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis id="6EE863067C392A400AFA8D3C4336A2AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">M. hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Illiger) (
<emphasis id="025046D15746ADBE86BA9A043F7905AD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">12, 15, 18</emphasis>
) male: aedeagus in ventral (
<emphasis id="9855C7D7724D164BEBACBFF5464A0219" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">10-12</emphasis>
) and lateral (
<emphasis id="CE67FF8D6AD31CF91ACCF95583EF7584" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">13-15</emphasis>
) views female: genital segments, dorsal part (
<emphasis id="26794EA25E2A6EE7F2A279E2FEBD0DFE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">16-18</emphasis>
) in ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
