<subSubSection id="B8E6DB93A47FA111445FB1AD14AF858D" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="628E3EC5FBB857A707490DE0936DBC93" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution and natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2B536B3CDE6A5B96AECA9AAD6A9D3EA3" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="79441D28988185CA669CBDF3D0BC847F" baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1794" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus hemipterus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemipterus">
<emphasis id="267AF45B0F69A89863B11F0D0F70961C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus hemipterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widespread member of the genus, with records ranging from the United Kingdom in the West to China, South Korea, Japan, and Far East Russia in the East (
<bibRefCitation id="D37452A03BCB5333CB71274096399825" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79957" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="475 - 524" refId="B3" refString="Cuccodoro, G, 1996. Revision of the Japanese rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae). Revue suisse de Zoologie 103 (2): 475 - 524, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79957" title="Revision of the Japanese rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.79957" volume="103" year="1996">Cuccodoro 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D5779078E73C6CD158B9AC965DE2BDC5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1347 - 1415" refId="B6" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Loebl, I, 1997. Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Journal of Natural History 31: 1347 - 1415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" title="Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" volume="31" year="1997">
Cuccodoro and 
<normalizedToken id="344015BE576646BCC79FA5C00954FA2C" originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C5AE2FB554F9A4CA32D88A32A0E1CD7C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/n11-004" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="317 - 331" refId="B7" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Kim, HM, Ahn, KJ, 2011. Megarthrus of Korea, with description of a new species (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). The Canadian Entomologist 143: 317 - 331, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/n11-004" title="Megarthrus of Korea, with description of a new species (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/n11-004" volume="143" year="2011">Cuccodoro et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It occurs in a wide range of microhabitats (carrion, fungi, leaf litter, and various types of decaying organic matter); in South Korea it was abundantly collected from fresh and rotten fungi. The first record for China without precise locality data (
<bibRefCitation id="DEE7FC9AC4560689A7CD36DCD8A72519" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" author="Cuccodoro, G" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1347 - 1415" refId="B6" refString="Cuccodoro, G, Loebl, I, 1997. Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae). Journal of Natural History 31: 1347 - 1415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" title="Revision of the Palaearctic rove-beetles of the genus Megarthrus Curtis (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Proteininae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939700770761" volume="31" year="1997">
Cuccodoro and 
<normalizedToken id="C11D8380D0D2B2C0245A5C31907F603C" originalValue="Löbl">Loebl</normalizedToken>
1997
</bibRefCitation>
) refers to the three specimens cited here from Chi-Kuan Shan from the Max 
<normalizedToken id="80B13F54902C7DA752219251AD77ECC0" originalValue="Bernhauer’s">Bernhauer's</normalizedToken>
collection, housed in the FMNH. The species, which occurs on most land masses surrounding the Sea of Japan, seems to reach its southern limit of extension in China in the Western Hills (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C61E98B22FD6E589E2B24D729274BC9D" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 41. Distribution map in China of Megarthrus dentipes Bernhauer, M. flavolimbatus Cameron, M. hemipterus (Illiger) and Megarthrus panda sp. nov. Scale bar: 300 km." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578551" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">41</figureCitation>
), where it was collected in mid-April at 1400 m a. s. l. from mixed woodland litter on Mount Dongling (Beijing).
</paragraph>
